{"slide_id": "5aed46f009ac84854c5c1cebd08f867d-DASH_Presentati__s3__G3_ALIGNMENT_OFFSET", "width": 960, "height": 540, "elements": [{"element_id": "shp141", "type": "title", "bbox": {"x": 283.82, "y": 48.54, "width": 466.32, "height": 72.65}, "text": "Satellite Product Analysis and Distribution Enterprise System (SPADES)", "style": {"font_size_pt": 16.0}, "z": 0, "placeholder_id": "TITLE (1)", "metadata": {"role": "TITLE (1)"}}, {"element_id": "shp142", "type": "body", "bbox": {"x": 33.52, "y": 143.52, "width": 917.51, "height": 247.18}, "text": "Configuration driven algorithm execution architecture used by both NCEI and SWPC for running algorithms. \nSWPC and NCEI have distinct implementations designed to interface with the algorithms in the same manner.\ne.g. SPADES-Demo used by NCEI is Java based, while SPADES-lite used by SWPC is Python based\nReal-time processing drives algorithm features:\nInputs are all present at run time\nMust be completed within a limited time frame\nNo hard coding directory paths or other parameters into the code\nSPADES Control Segment manages algorithms through JSON configuration files:\nConfigurable Business Logic (CBL) \nRun Level Configuration (RLC)", "style": {"font_size_pt": 11.0}, "z": 1, "placeholder_id": "BODY (2)", "metadata": {"role": "BODY (2)"}}, {"element_id": "shp143", "type": "image", "bbox": {"x": 827.36, "y": 17.89, "width": 99.12, "height": 124.41}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 2, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp144", "type": "shape", "bbox": {"x": 741.24, "y": 206.68, "width": 220.66, "height": 42.02}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 3, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp145", "type": "shape", "bbox": {"x": 682.97, "y": 173.15, "width": 268.06, "height": 16.16}, "text": "", "style": {}, "z": 4, "placeholder_id": null, "metadata": {}}, {"element_id": "shp146", "type": "body", "bbox": {"x": 4.81, "y": 374.06, "width": 143.87, "height": 42.02}, "text": "Science Team", "